{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Water}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Luvdisc}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Water|prevnum=369|prev=Relicanth|nextnum=371|next=Bagon|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Luvdisc}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Luvdisc\n|jname=ラブカス\n|jtranslit=Rabukasu\n|tmname=Lovecus\n|ndex=370\n|hdex=183\n|hdex6=192\n|karea=Coastal\n|kdex=029\n|adex=111\n|fbrow=120\n|obrow=059\n|type1=Water\n|category=Rendezvous\n|height-ftin=2\'00"\n|height-m=0.6\n|weight-lbs=19.2\n|weight-kg=8.7\n|ability1=Swift Swim\n|abilityd=Hydration\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Water 2\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=1\n|evsp=1\n|expyield=116\n|oldexp=110\n|lv100exp=800,000\n|gendercode=191\n|color=Pink\n|catchrate=225\n|body=03\n|pokefordex=luvdisc\n|generation=3\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Luvdisc\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ラブカス\'\'\' \'\'Lovecus\'\') is a {{type|Water}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation III]].\n\nIt is not known to [[Evolution|evolve]] into or from any other Pokémon.\n\n==Biology==\nLuvdisc is a fish-like Pokémon with a relatively flat body in the shape of a heart. Loving couples gave this Pokémon its name after spotting it in the ocean waters. It is primarily light pink, with pale lips and circular markings on its cheeks. During the spring, it forms groups that turn the ocean\'s surface bright pink. Luvdisc lives in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Sea Pokémon|warm seas}}, where it makes its nest in the branches of {{p|Corsola}} or coral reefs. As shown in \'\'[[HS16|Luvdisc is a Many Splendored Thing!]]\'\', when two Luvdisc kiss, they are able to use their slender bodies as wings in order to fly for short periods of time. {{p|Pelipper}} is a natural predator of Luvdisc.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Luvdisc anime.png|left|thumb|250px|Luvdisc in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[Caserin and Luverin]]=====\nBoth {{an|Misty}} and {{an|Daisy}} have a Luvdisc, [[nickname]]d Caserin and Luverin, respectively. They acquired the two Rendezvous Pokémon sometime prior to \'\'[[HS16|Luvdisc is a Many Splendored Thing!]]\'\'. They found themselves the target of [[Butch]] and [[Cassidy]] under instructions from [[Dr. Namba]].\n\n=====Other=====\nA Luvdisc debuted in \'\'[[AG110|The Great Eight Fate!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Juan]]. It was used in [[AG111|the following episode]], during his [[Gym]] {{pkmn|battle}} against {{Ash}}. Luvdisc first battled {{AP|Grovyle}} and won, but later lost against {{AP|Corphish}}.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nMultiple Luvdisc debuted in \'\'[[AG093|Clamperl of Wisdom]]\'\' as some of the Pokémon living at [[Maisie Island]].\n\nMultiple {{pkmn2|wild}} Luvdisc appeared of \'\'[[M09|Pokémon Ranger and the Temple of the Sea]]\'\'. They were among the Pokémon present during the final showdown with [[The Phantom]] and his crew. They briefly reappeared in a montage in \'\'[[M10|The Rise of Darkrai]]\'\', which chronicled the preceding nine {{pkmn|movie}}s.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in the opening sequence of \'\'[[M11|Giratina and the Sky Warrior]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[DP113|Hold the Phione!]]\'\' as residents of [[Chocovine Town]].\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in the opening sequence of \'\'[[M13|Zoroark: Master of Illusions]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[XY001|Kalos, Where Dreams and Adventures Begin!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[XY022|Going for the Gold!]]\'\', where they were among the Pokémon seen in the {{DL|Ambrette Town|Ambrette Aquarium}}.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[XY024|An Undersea Place to Call Home!]]\'\', where they were among the Pokémon who made the wreck of the [[S.S. Cussler]] their home.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[M17|Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM001|Alola to New Adventure!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM002|The Guardian\'s Challenge!]]\'\', \'\'[[SM006|A Shocking Grocery Run!]]\'\', \'\'[[SM007|That\'s Why the Litten is a Scamp!]]\'\', \'\'[[SM024|Alolan Open House!]]\'\', \'\'[[SM044|A Dream Encounter!]]\'\', \'\'[[SM048|Night of a Thousand Poses!]]\'\', \'\'[[SM055|The Professors\' New Adventure!]]\'\', \'\'[[SM057|The Dex Can\'t Help It!]]\'\', and \'\'[[SM081|A Young Royal Flame Ignites!]]\'\', where they were residing in {{an|Professor Kukui}}\'s lab alongside a {{p|Corsola}}.\n\nFive Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM005|Yo, Ho, Ho! Go, Popplio!]]\'\', with two of them appearing in a fantasy.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM012|The Sun, the Scare, the Secret Lair!]]\'\'.\n\nA Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM022|A Shivering Shovel Search!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM031|The Island Whisperer!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM040|Balloons, Brionne, and Belligerence!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM045|Now You See Them, Now You Don\'t!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM048|Night of a Thousand Poses!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM056|Let Sleeping Pokémon Lie!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM071|Dewpider Ascending!]]\'\'. They were swimming in the ocean before they were scared away by a {{p|Sharpedo}}.\n\nA Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM087|Filling the Light with Darkness!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM112|Got Meltan?]]\'\'.\n\nA Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM120|The One That Didn\'t Get Away!]]\'\', where it was caught by {{an|Lillie}} whilst [[fishing]].\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[SM126|Pikachu\'s Exciting Adventure!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in a fantasy in [[SM145]].\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexbody|AG110|Luvdisc|May\'s Pokédex|Luvdisc, the Rendezvous Pokémon. Luvdisc group together during {{pkmn|breeding}} season, covering the surface of the ocean in a brilliant pink.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Advanced Generation\'\'|Hoenn}}\n\n===In Pokémon Generations===\n[[File:Horsea Luvdisc PG.png|thumb|250px|Luvdisc in [[Pokémon Generations]]]]\nMultiple {{pkmn2|wild}} Luvdisc appeared in \'\'[[PG08|The Cavern]]\'\', where they were seen in the waters that surrounded the [[Mossdeep Space Center]].\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Wallace Elizabeth.png|200px|thumb|Luvdisc in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n[[Wallace]] has a Luvdisc [[nickname]]d Elizabeth that debuted in \'\'[[PS222|Short Shift for Shiftry]]\'\'. She is usually shown out of her [[Poké Ball]], floating along beside him. Wallace relies on her to solve problems, as she is shown doing such things as putting out a burning scarf and releasing a {{p|Lileep}} and {{p|Anorith}} to test {{adv|Ruby}}\'s worth at Wallace\'s request. Also, the two seem to share a bond, as he rarely, if ever, has to specify what he wants her to do. Like all of Wallace\'s Pokémon in the manga, she is incredibly beautiful and was able to defeat all of Ruby\'s top Contest Pokémon, excluding [[Feefee]], in an unofficial Contest in a matter of minutes.\n\nWallace\'s mentor, [[Juan]], uses a pair of Luvdisc that first appeared in \'\'[[PS256|With a Spoink in Your Step II]]\'\'. They observe him as he trained Ruby and {{adv|Sapphire}}.\n\nThe {{OBP|Battle Tower|Generation III}} rented a Luvdisc, which was stolen by [[Guile Hideout]] in \'\'[[PS334|The Final Battle VII]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Luvdisc appeared in [[PS541]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Omega Ruby Crimson Passion and Pokémon Alpha Sapphire Indigo Wisdom manga===\nSome Luvdisc appeared while {{OBP|Alpha|CPIW}} and {{OBP|Omega|CPIW}} {{m|Dive|dove}} underwater with their {{p|Wailmer}}.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Luvdisc (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n* [[Pokémon: Magikarp Jump]]: A Luvdisc may appear as part of the "Lost Luvdisc" {{DL|Pokémon: Magikarp Jump|Random encounter events|event}}, where it will give the player 4 Diamonds. Several Luvdisc also appear as part of the "Food Fever" event, swimming in and leaving food in the pond.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Water}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=III}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=III|reg1=Hoenn|num1=183|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ruby|t=FFF|entry=Luvdisc live in shallow seas in the tropics. This heart-shaped Pokémon earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the ocean\'s waves.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=Luvdisc\'s heart-shaped body is a symbol of love and romance. It is said that any couple meeting this Pokémon is promised a loving relationship that never ends.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Emerald|t=FFF|entry=Luvdisc make the branches of {{p|Corsola}} their nests. There is a custom from long ago of giving a Luvdisc as a gift to express one\'s feelings of love.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=FireRed|v2=LeafGreen|entry=During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=IV|reg1=Sinnoh|reg2=Johto}}\n{{Dex/Entry3|v=Diamond|v2=Pearl|v3=Platinum|entry=It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=HeartGold|v2=SoulSilver|entry=Its heart-shaped body makes it popular. In some places, you would give a Luvdisc to someone you love.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=V|reg1=Unova}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black|t=FFF|v2=White|entry=It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|t=FFF|v2=White 2|entry=It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=029|label1=Coastal|reg2=Hoenn|num2=192}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the w